# Police Complaint AI Assistant — Optimized Beginner-Friendly Plan

## 1. Project Goal

Build a simple AI-powered police complaint assistant.

The user will enter a complaint in natural language. The AI will understand the complaint, classify it, extract important details, ask relevant follow-up questions, assign priority, and save the complaint.

This project should look AI-powered, but the codebase should stay small and beginner-friendly.

## 2. Final Tech Stack

```text
Frontend: Streamlit
Backend: FastAPI
AI: LangChain + Groq API
Storage: SQLite
Dashboard: Simple Streamlit records page
```

Do not use:

```text
RAG
Vector DB
LangGraph
PDF generation
Analytics dashboard
Admin authentication
Local LLM
Complaint status tracking
Anonymous reporting
```

## 3. Final Project Pipeline

```text
User enters complaint
→ Streamlit sends complaint to FastAPI
→ FastAPI calls AI service
→ AI classifies complaint
→ AI extracts location, time, persons, and summary
→ Backend selects follow-up questions
→ Backend assigns priority
→ Complaint is saved in SQLite
→ Streamlit shows complaint summary
→ Records page displays saved complaints
```

## 4. Why AI Is Needed

Without AI, this is just a complaint form.

The AI is useful because users may write messy natural language.

Example user complaint:

```text
Yesterday night near Tambaram, one car hit a bike and the rider was bleeding badly.
```

AI should extract:

```text
Category: road accident
Location: Tambaram
Time: yesterday night
Persons involved: car driver, bike rider
Priority: high
Follow-up question: Were there any injuries or fatalities?
```

So the website is only the interface. The AI is the brain that understands the complaint.

## 5. Final Features

### Feature 1: Complaint Submission

User enters a complaint in Streamlit.

Example:

```text
A child is missing near school since evening.
```

### Feature 2: AI Classification

AI classifies the complaint into one category.

Allowed categories:

```text
child safety
cyber crime incident
women help desk
public healthcare
road accident
murder / serious crime incident
fire accident
general issue recorded
```

If the AI is not sure, use:

```text
general issue recorded
```

### Feature 3: Entity Extraction

AI extracts:

```text
location
incident_time
persons_involved
summary
```

### Feature 4: Follow-Up Questions

The system asks follow-up questions based on the category.

Example for road accident:

```text
Where did the accident occur?
What time did the accident happen?
What vehicles were involved?
Were there any injuries?
Are there any witnesses?
```

### Feature 5: Priority Assignment

Priority should be assigned using simple Python rules, not fully by AI.

Priority values:

```text
High
Medium
Low
```

Example rules:

```text
child safety → High
murder / serious crime incident → High
fire accident → High
road accident with injury → High
cyber crime incident → Medium
general issue recorded → Low
```

### Feature 6: SQLite Storage

Save the complaint after AI processing.

Stored fields:

```text
id
complaint_text
category
location
incident_time
persons_involved
summary
priority
followup_questions
created_at
```

### Feature 7: Complaint Records Page

Simple Streamlit page to view saved complaints.

Show:

```text
Complaint ID
Category
Location
Priority
Summary
Created time
```

This is not a full admin dashboard. It is only a simple records page.

